{\pos(196,180)}纸牌屋

11
00:01:32,950 --> 00:01:35,910
{\an2}{\pos(211.4,243.15)}第三季  第七集

12
00:01:48,190 --> 00:01:49,260
你是否愿意再次确认
Do you renew your commitment

13
00:01:49,270 --> 00:01:51,680
与这名女子结为合法夫妇的承诺
to this woman as your lawful wedded wife,

14
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:55,440
爱她  尊敬她  照顾她
to love her, honor her, comfort her,

15
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:58,250
无论罹病或安康
keep her in sickness and in health,

16
00:01:58,650 --> 00:02:00,980
心无二意  忠于她
forsaking all others, be true to her,

17
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,990
直到生命尽头
as long as you both shall live?

18
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:05,380
我愿意
I do.

19
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:08,660
你是否愿意再次确认
Do you renew your commitment to this man

20
00:02:08,930 --> 00:02:10,710
与这名男子结为合法夫妇的承诺
as your lawful wedded husband,

21
00:02:11,100 --> 00:02:14,310
爱他  尊敬他  照顾他
to love him, honor him, comfort him,

22
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:16,910
无论罹病或安康
keep him in sickness and in health,

23
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,500
心无二意  忠于他
forsaking all others, be true to him,

24
00:02:19,890 --> 00:02:22,020
直到生命尽头
as long as you both shall live?

25
00:02:23,220 --> 00:02:24,050
我愿意
I do.

26
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:27,860
愿这再次确认的承诺  能加深你们的爱情
May this renewed commitment deepen your love for each other

27
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,660
让你们的婚姻更加坚固  直到永远
and strengthen your eternal bond.

28
00:02:50,550 --> 00:02:51,560
弗兰西斯
Francis?

29
00:02:54,390 --> 00:02:56,640
把尸体抬下去时不要拍照
No photographs when they unload his body.

30
00:02:56,640 --> 00:02:57,950
能答应我吗
Will you promise me that?

31
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:27,940
{\pos(99.6,47.7)}{\an7}第一夫人反抗佩特罗夫

32
00:03:29,770 --> 00:03:31,840
很多人说你是英雄呢
A lot of people are calling you a hero.

33
00:03:34,110 --> 00:03:35,490
也有很多人不那么看
A lot of people aren't.

34
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:02,230
弗兰西斯  我会让维和决议案
Francis, I will get this peacekeeping resolution

35
00:04:02,230 --> 00:04:04,050
在联合国大会上通过的
passed through the General Assembly.

36
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,510
这是我欠你的
I owe you that.

37
00:04:13,010 --> 00:04:16,880
我们明天要为总统像拍照
So we have the photograph tomorrow for the presidential portrait.

38
00:04:17,210 --> 00:04:19,230
他们要靠这个画像
It's what they're gonna base the painting on.

39
00:04:22,260 --> 00:04:24,010
我要笑  你呢
I'll be smiling. Will you?

40
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,970
他们干什么呢
What are they doing?

41
00:04:33,890 --> 00:04:37,000
是文化交流  跟西藏
Part of a... cultural exchange, sir, with Tibet.

42
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:38,480
他们会待一个月
They'll be here for a month.

43
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:40,200
一个月
A month?

44
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,860
别担心  你的字是鬼画符
Don't worry, your handwriting's atrocious.

45
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:22,000
什么都看不懂
Couldn't read a thing.

46
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:25,040
-汤姆  -我知道  凯特·鲍德温
- Tom. - I know. Kate Baldwin.

47
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:25,890
我知道
I know.

48
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:27,450
我们真不错
Gold stars for us.

49
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:28,600
两个月
It only took two months

50
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,080
同乘一架飞机  总算互相介绍了
riding on the same plane to introduce ourselves.

51
00:05:31,100 --> 00:05:32,170
或许我就是害羞呢
Maybe I'm shy.

52
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,600
才不是  你就是不屑于跟平头百姓打交道
Oh, no, you're not. You just don't mingle with the peasants.

53
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:38,320
要说我们谁是平头百姓  那也是我
If one of us is a peasant, I think it's me.

54
00:05:50,030 --> 00:05:52,320
抱歉我不能留在加夫尼陪你
I'm sorry I can't stay here in Gaffney with you.

55
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,400
没事
It's okay.

56
00:05:55,290 --> 00:05:56,280
我们明天见
I'll see you tomorrow.

57
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:58,920
或许今晚就能见  如果顺利
Maybe tonight, if all goes well.

58
00:06:00,330 --> 00:06:01,650
觉得乐观吗
Feeling optimistic?

59
00:06:02,470 --> 00:06:03,960
我给了你一个承诺
I made you a promise.

60
00:06:07,630 --> 00:06:09,580
走吧  飞机等着你呢
Well, go on. You have a plane waiting.

61
00:06:12,410 --> 00:06:13,190
谢谢
Thank you.

62
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:18,690
汤姆
Tom.

63
00:06:37,900 --> 00:06:39,190
共和党要引入一份
The Republicans are introducing a bill

64
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,700
《斯塔福德法案》的修正案
that amends the Stafford Act.

65
00:06:41,450 --> 00:06:43,250
他们说用联邦应急管理署的资金
They say that the siphoning of FEMA funds

66
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,170
来资助《美国就业法案》有违拨款法规
for America Works violates the appropriation.

67
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:46,330
让他们去吧
So let them.

68
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,830
两党都会支持
It's got bipartisan support.

69
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,800
邓巴会公开支持修正案
Dunbar's going to publicly support the bill.

70
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,740
-杰姬呢  -她不想搅进去
- What about Jackie? - She's trying to stay out of it,

71
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:54,170
但如果投票了  她只能随大流
but if it goes to a vote, she's gotta go with the tide.

72
00:06:54,370 --> 00:06:55,110
她的民调数字
We don't want her poll numbers

73
00:06:55,110 --> 00:06:57,290
刚刚开始追上邓巴  不能这时受挫
to take a hit as she's starting to gain on Dunbar.

74
00:06:57,290 --> 00:06:58,680
如果他们通过修正案  我就否决
If they pass the bill, I'll veto it.

75
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,910
他们推翻  我就拒绝执行
If they override, I'll refuse to enforce.

76
00:07:00,910 --> 00:07:02,620
等闹到最高法院
By the time it gets to the Supreme Court,

77
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:03,690
我们已经可以拿出就业成果了
we'll have jobs to show,

78
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:05,070
他们只能耍嘴皮子
they'll have nothing but rhetoric.

79
00:07:05,070 --> 00:07:07,320
这是公关战  与法律无关
This is a public relations battle, not a legal one.

80
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:07,900
发声明吗
Statement?

81
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:09,830
就我说的  火药味儿轻点
Just what I just said, less combative.

82
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:13,260
我们怎么拍
So, how do we want to do this?

83
00:07:13,260 --> 00:07:15,920
我认为第一夫人应该坐着  您站在她身后
I think the First Lady should sit. You behind her.

84
00:07:16,370 --> 00:07:18,010
这样可以吗  安德伍德夫人
Does that work for you, Mrs. Underwood?

85
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:19,710
当然  效果好就行
Uh, yes, whatever works best.

86
00:07:20,420 --> 00:07:22,920
我先为夫人调灯光  然后给您找位置  先生
Let me adjust the light for her, and then I'll place you, sir.

87
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:25,570
非洲集团给
The African bloc just added

88
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,550
维和决议案加了一项条款
a provision to the peacekeeping resolution.

89
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:28,550
什么内容
What does it say?

90
00:07:29,180 --> 00:07:31,510
要求非洲指挥维和军队
Requires African command of the forces.

91
00:07:31,710 --> 00:07:33,430
这是故意坏事  弗兰西斯
It's a poison pill, Francis.

92
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,630
以色列和巴勒斯坦都不可能同意
There's no way Israel or Palestine will get on board with that.

93
00:07:36,630 --> 00:07:38,370
你觉得是俄罗斯在指使吗
You think the Russians are behind it?

94
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:41,690
可能吧  凯茜和我还在调查
Probably. Cathy and I are investigating.

95
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,520
好了  总统先生  请站在您妻子身后
All right, Mr. President. Just behind your wife, please.

96
00:07:51,450 --> 00:07:52,760
不要我放吗
Do you prefer I not?

97
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:54,050
什么
What?

98
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:56,390
您放手的位置很好
Where you had your hand is perfect.

99
00:07:58,140 --> 00:08:00,870
很好  好了  拍了
Great. All right. Here we go.

100
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,650
请再笑一点
A little more of a smile, please.

101
00:08:10,810 --> 00:08:11,630
请进
Come in.

102
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:18,110
今天有进展吗
Any luck today?

103
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:22,990
莫里科夫  说不是他们
Moryakov... says it wasn't them.

104
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:26,080
我倒不怎么相信他
Not that I trust him.

105
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:31,310
现在我只能设法让津巴布韦开口了
So now I just need to see if I can get Zimbabwe to talk.

106
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:37,990
今天  我们拍照的时候
Today, when we took the photo...

107
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:42,020
我碰了你的肩
I touched your shoulder.

108
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,190
怎么了
Yes?

109
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,190
你躲了一下
You flinched.

110
00:08:48,550 --> 00:08:50,510
-什么  -我感觉到了
- What? - I felt it.

111
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,010
没有啊
No, I didn't.

112
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,510
就好像...
It was like...

113
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,040
你缩了一下
you recoiled.

114
00:09:03,330 --> 00:09:05,580
我觉得你是想多了
I think you're reading too much into something

115
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,580
而且我觉得根本没这回事
that I don't think actually happened.

116
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,960
好吧  当我没说过
All right. Forget I said anything.

117
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:18,170
等等
Wait.

118
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,130
我就是...
I just...

119
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:25,950
算了  我也不知道我是想说什么
Never mind. I don't know what I was gonna say.

120
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:35,620
晚安
Good night.

121
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,290
房子应该就在那边
House must've been somewhere out there.

122
00:10:30,010 --> 00:10:31,310
如果能算得上是房子
Well, if you can call it a house.

123
00:10:31,310 --> 00:10:33,010
不比那辆卡车大多少
It was no bigger than that truck.

124
00:10:34,110 --> 00:10:36,630
农场完全拆了  这倒也好
Nothing left of the farm, which is for the best.

125
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:39,430
桃树在这里都不结果
Peaches didn't want to grow here anyway.

126
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,570
在表土下两英尺就是石头的地上
That's what you get for planting on land

127
00:10:42,570 --> 00:10:46,470
种东西  还能有什么好结果
with solid rock two feet below the topsoil.

128
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:48,420
这事我们应该
You know, that's one of the points

129
00:10:48,420 --> 00:10:50,140
在书里提及
that we should make in the book,

130
00:10:50,370 --> 00:10:53,380
在合适的环境里辛勤劳作才能有结果
that hard work is only worth it in the right conditions.

131
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:56,130
我们想帮助大家成功
We want to set people up for success.

132
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:59,690
职业培训  合理的职业道路
Vocational training, legitimate career paths.

133
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:09,460
欢迎回来  加夫尼怎么样
Welcome back. How was Gaffney?

134
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:11,960
我们跟卡斯皮大使安排时间了吗
Do we have a time set for Ambassador Caspi yet?

135
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,400
她办公室那边在拖
Her office is stalling.

136
00:11:13,970 --> 00:11:15,860
跟她约好  她在哪方便见面都行
Get her schedule. We'll go wherever she is.

137
00:11:15,860 --> 00:11:17,780
她应该会参加今晚的鸡尾酒会
I think she'll be at the cocktail reception tonight

138
00:11:17,780 --> 00:11:20,190
-在墨西哥领事馆  -我去打电话确认
- at the Mexican Consulate. - I'll call and find out.

139
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:22,550
那是什么
What's that?

140
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,530
今早寄来给你的
It came in for you this morning.

141
00:11:25,130 --> 00:11:26,130
弗兰西斯吗
Francis?

142
00:11:26,210 --> 00:11:28,640
约翰·帕斯特纳克  迈克尔·科里根的丈夫
John Pasternak. Michael Corrigan's husband.

143
00:11:29,450 --> 00:11:32,100
最新的采访请求放在你桌上了
The latest pile of interview requests is on your desk,

144
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,900
大都跟科里根事件有关
most of them Corrigan related.

145
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:36,060
反歧视同性恋联盟希望你去他们的
And GLAAD wants you to be a keynote speaker

146
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:37,910
媒体颁奖典礼做主讲人
at their Media Awards Ceremony.

147
00:11:37,910 --> 00:11:38,900
他怎么知道的
How did he know?

148
00:11:39,230 --> 00:11:41,740
你婚誓重证的事吗  新闻上有
About your vows? It's been in the news.

149
00:11:41,740 --> 00:11:43,850
不是  我喜欢郁金香的事
No, that I liked tulips.

150
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:54,280
恭喜婚誓重证
爱情恒久远
约·帕

151
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:53,850
你母亲工作吗
Did your mother work?

152
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:55,780
主要是做女仆
As a maid, mostly.

153
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:57,970
她挺受欢迎  因为她是白人
In high demand, because she was white.

154
00:11:58,340 --> 00:12:00,690
大家认定她不会偷贵重东西
People assumed she wouldn't steal any valuables,

155
00:12:00,690 --> 00:12:01,870
但她当然还是偷了
but of course she did.

156
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:08,320
我记得有一晚  她回家时拿着两枚蓝宝石耳环
I remember one night, she came home with two sapphire earrings.

157
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,980
第二天她拿去了斯帕坦堡的当铺
She took them to the pawn shop in Spartanburg the next day,

158
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:14,390
但前一晚她戴了一整晚  睡觉也没摘
but she wore them all night long, even slept in them.

159
00:12:15,540 --> 00:12:16,340
她大概是想知道
I guess she wanted to know

160
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:18,560
戴真珠宝是什么感觉
what it felt like to have real jewelry,

161
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:20,500
哪怕只是几小时
even if it was just for a few hours.

162
00:12:21,590 --> 00:12:23,350
这可别写进书里
That does not go in the book.

163
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:27,250
你父母怎么不多生几个孩子
Why didn't your parents have any more kids?

164
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:29,380
这跟我们的话题无关
That's not relevant to what we're doing.

165
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:30,870
我只是想了解你的家庭
I'm just trying to get a sense of your family.

166
00:12:30,870 --> 00:12:33,150
谷仓应该就在那边
The barn must've been somewhere right over there.

167
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:36,770
我父亲以前会躲进谷仓避开我们
My father used to escape in there to get away from us.

168
00:12:37,050 --> 00:12:38,940
一般还带一瓶酒进去
Usually brought a bottle with him.

169
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,810
你爱你父亲吗
Did you love your father?

170
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:43,170
他内心深处是个好人
He was a good man, down deep.

171
00:12:43,170 --> 00:12:44,580
他十分爱我们
He cared for us greatly.

172
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:46,900
努力工作  供养家庭
Worked hard to put food on the table.

173
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,820
并不能总能做到  但并非他不努力
Didn't always succeed, but that wasn't for a lack of trying.

174
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,830
瞧  这不是回答
See... that's not an answer.

175
00:12:54,010 --> 00:12:55,980
我问你你是否爱你父亲  你却不说
I asked you if you loved your father, you don't tell me.

176
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:58,390
你只说你希望我写的东西
You tell me what you want me to write.

177
00:12:58,450 --> 00:13:00,580
你从一开始就是这样
Which is what you've done since the beginning.

178
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,590
你该开始说实话了
It's time to start telling the truth.

179
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:05,330
-你觉得我一直在撒谎吗  -我确定
- You think I've been lying? - I know you have.

180
00:13:05,330 --> 00:13:09,260
你唯一没撒谎的一次  是在白宫那一晚
The only time you haven't is that one night in the White House.

181
00:13:09,270 --> 00:13:11,910
我经历的最糟的一次历险  我告诉你们
The worst adventure I've ever been on. I can promise you...

182
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:14,310
-我不明白  -这游戏赢不了
- I don't get it. - The game is unwinnable.

183
00:13:16,410 --> 00:13:18,680
-那有什么意义  -意义就在这里
- What is the point? - That is the point.

184
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,360
我认为我们
I find it unlikely that

185
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:23,030
如果反复重新开始  是不可能进步的
we'll ever progress by starting over and over again.

186
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,960
-但总得比这强  -天呐
- But it's got to be better than this. - Oh, God.

187
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:26,950
我们试试吧  何不呢
Okay, let's give it a shot. Why not?

188
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:31,370
-有件事很明确  -又重启了
- Something was very clear. - It just started over again.

189
00:13:31,370 --> 00:13:33,090
总是一遍遍重启
It keeps doing that over and over.

190
00:13:34,210 --> 00:13:36,060
你无视他的指示  他就让你从头开始
Ignore his instructions, he sends you back.

191
00:13:36,060 --> 00:13:38,320
如果我遵照指示呢
What if I follow his instructions?

192
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:42,150
混乱一片  完全随机
Chaos takes over. Randomness.

193
00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:44,730
根本无法遵从规则
It's impossible to follow the rules.

194
00:13:44,730 --> 00:13:47,410
下次吧  这太接近我的现实生活了
Another time. It's too much like my real life.

195
00:13:49,580 --> 00:13:51,560
再说  我们不该玩游戏
Besides, we shouldn't be playing games.

196
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:53,490
你应该向我提问
You should be asking me questions.

197
00:13:53,950 --> 00:13:55,190
你要把我灌醉了
You're getting me drunk.

198
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,930
我肯定要记不住我问了什么了
I won't remember what I asked.

199
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:03,890
我上次喝得这么醉  我闯进了一座图书馆
The last time I got this drunk, I broke into a library.

200
00:14:04,070 --> 00:14:06,680
在查尔斯顿  我母校
In Charleston, my alma mater.

201
00:14:06,710 --> 00:14:07,940
桑蒂诺
The Sentinel.

202
00:14:09,010 --> 00:14:10,890
我差点吐在自己身上
I almost puked all over myself.

203
00:14:10,890 --> 00:14:13,280
第八章  《总统大吐》
That's Chapter Eight: "POTUS Blows Chunks."

204
00:14:17,110 --> 00:14:18,610
能小点声吗
Can you keep it down, please?

205
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,030
-一起来嘛  -抱歉
- Come join us. - So sorry.

206
00:14:22,030 --> 00:14:24,400
-我都睡了  -这样啊...
- I was asleep. - Oh. We'll...

207
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,440
-我们去书房  -谢谢
- We'll move into the study. - Thank you.

208
00:14:45,830 --> 00:14:46,800
弗兰西斯
Francis?

209
00:14:48,230 --> 00:14:50,020
我就去
I'll be right there in a minute.

210
00:14:52,940 --> 00:14:54,660
我不喜欢让他来这里
I don't like him being up here.

211
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,760
我们会小点声的
We'll be more quiet.

212
00:14:58,220 --> 00:15:00,130
这是我们私人的空间
This is our private space.

213
00:15:00,590 --> 00:15:02,800
-他是我的客人  -他是个陌生人
- He's my guest. - He's a stranger.

214
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:08,660
好吧  今晚之后  再不请他来了
All right. After tonight, no more.

215
00:15:09,670 --> 00:15:11,300
我不是不讲理
I'm not being unreasonable.

216
00:15:16,070 --> 00:15:17,270
我该...
I should've...

217
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:21,890
意识到我们是多吵
realized how much noise we were making.

218
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,350
能问你个问题吗
Can I ask you a question?

219
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:29,940
你不就是来问问题的吗
Well, that's what you're here for, isn't it?

220
00:15:34,260 --> 00:15:35,860
你们怎么不睡一个屋
Why don't you sleep in the same room?

221
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:43,380
我们搬过来
Uh, that just sorta happened over...

222
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:47,310
几个月后  就开始了
a few months after we moved in here.

223
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:49,440
一切都还好吗
Everything okay?

224
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:50,940
你俩之间
Between you two?

225
00:15:51,390 --> 00:15:52,560
当然
Oh, you bet.

226
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:58,170
虽然不算最好的时候
Well, it's been better.

227
00:16:02,350 --> 00:16:03,900
不  不太好
No, it's not okay.

228
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:09,690
你俩从莫斯科回程时的争执
The fight. Coming back from Moscow.

229
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,520
你听到了
You heard us?

230
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:15,830
只听到吵嚷声  听不清话
The yelling. Not what you said.

231
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:22,730
我们不怎么吵架
We don't fight often, but, uh...

232
00:16:28,410 --> 00:16:29,420
但这一次
This one...

233
00:16:32,390 --> 00:16:34,180
总是揭旧伤疤
scabs keep coming off.

234
00:16:37,450 --> 00:16:39,080
我们说了些过分的话
We said things.

235
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,700
无法收回的话
Things you just can't take back.

236
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:50,480
很晚了  我们到此为止吧
It's late. We should call it a night.

237
00:17:03,290 --> 00:17:04,210
托马斯
Thomas.

238
00:17:08,630 --> 00:17:10,930
我对低俗内容没兴趣
I have no interest in salaciousness.

239
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:23,170
8月14日是罗斯福新政的纪念日
August fourteenth is the anniversary of the New Deal.

240
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:25,340
届时要达到两万
I'd like to hit 20,000 by that date.

241
00:17:25,340 --> 00:17:26,410
应该没问题  先生
I believe we can do that, sir.

242
00:17:26,410 --> 00:17:27,450
雷米  参议院用来挑战
Remy, what's the timeline

243
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:29,620
联邦应急管理署拨款合法性的修正案的进度如何
on the Senate bill outlawing FEMA funds?

244
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:30,930
立法办公室预测参议院法案
The Leg office predicts the Senate version

245
00:17:30,930 --> 00:17:32,580
将在两三周内通过
will pass in two to three weeks.

246
00:17:32,580 --> 00:17:34,150
我们在跟国会内的盟友想办法
Working with friendlies in the House.

247
00:17:34,150 --> 00:17:35,780
搞点破坏  拖慢进度
Throw some pork on it, slow it down.

248
00:17:35,910 --> 00:17:37,900
所以我们更该加速进展了
That's all the more reason that we need to accelerate.

249
00:17:37,910 --> 00:17:39,260
如果我要否决这项法案
If I'm gonna veto this bill,

250
00:17:39,410 --> 00:17:43,120
一定要拿阻碍五万人就业为理由
I want it to be because it's gonna kill 50,000 new jobs.

251
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:45,230
-我们创造的就业机会  -是  先生
- Jobs that we created. - Yes, sir.

252
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:46,420
凯茜
Cathy?

253
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:49,650
俄罗斯在约旦河谷问题上仍不肯妥协
The Russians remain intransigent on the Jordan Valley.

254
00:17:49,650 --> 00:17:51,080
大使在努力
The ambassador is working hard

255
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:53,240
推动联合国大会就
to push the peacekeeping resolution to a vote

256
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:55,350
-维和决议案投票  -为什么延迟了
- by the General Assembly. - Why the delay?

257
00:17:55,610 --> 00:17:57,610
我们无法说服非洲集团
We're having a hard time getting the African bloc

258
00:17:57,610 --> 00:17:59,420
去掉坏事的条款
to remove the poison pill provision.

259
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:01,810
我们认为是以色列搞的鬼  他们临阵怯场
We think Israel's behind it. They got cold feet,

260
00:18:01,810 --> 00:18:02,910
便让非洲集团
convinced the African bloc

261
00:18:02,910 --> 00:18:05,610
破坏决议案进程  他们好下台
to sabotage the resolution so they have an out.

262
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:07,680
要我去跟总理谈谈吗
Do I need to speak to the Prime Minister?

263
00:18:07,680 --> 00:18:10,000
以色列大使已经否认了
Uh, the Israeli ambassador has already denied.

264
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,670
我觉得我们该专注于条款本身
I think we need to keep our focus on the provision itself.

265
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:13,760
好吧
All right.

266
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,830
非洲集团的首领是津巴布韦
The head of the African bloc is Zimbabwe.

267
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:17,400
我们认为以色列保证
And we believe Israel has promised

268
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:20,410
给他们一个价值可观的艾滋防治援助项目
them a sizable aid package for HIV prevention.

269
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:21,900
国务卿和我建议
The Secretary and I recommend

270
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,310
提高我们给津巴布韦的救济金
increasing our relief funds to Zimbabwe.

271
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:25,470
超过以色列人
Outspend the Israelis.

272
00:18:25,470 --> 00:18:27,700
金培图总统只会把钱中饱私囊
Well, President Chimbetu will just pocket the money.

273
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:30,120
我们早预计会遇到一定程度的腐败
Well, we always anticipate a certain level of graft.

274
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:33,810
一定程度  他是个贪婪透顶的恶魔
A certain level? He's egregious. The man's a monster.

275
00:18:33,810 --> 00:18:35,300
可他是非洲集团的首领
Who happens to run the African bloc.

276
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:37,600
他是个要么屠杀人民  要么盗取他们财产的人
Who happens to kill his people when he's not stealing from them,

277
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,360
所以我才缩减了对津巴布韦的救济
which is why I reduced aid to Zimbabwe.

278
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:42,380
如果我们想让他撤销条款  我们就得有点筹码
If we want him to remove the amendment, we have to be persuasive.

279
00:18:42,380 --> 00:18:45,180
我们已经在为《美就法》想方设法凑钱了
We are scraping together every penny we can to save AmWorks.

280
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:46,410
我最不需要的
The last thing I want

281
00:18:46,410 --> 00:18:48,940
就是因为从国际开发署拨款给
is to be slammed for giving additional money

282
00:18:48,940 --> 00:18:51,280
一个我想讨好的残忍独裁者
to a brutal dictator from USAID

283
00:18:51,290 --> 00:18:53,700
而遭到抨击  这想法太糟了
just to persuade him. This is ill-conceived.

284
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:56,350
你提出这样的提议之前该三思
You should think before you bring a proposal such as this.

285
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:59,430
我们会考虑其他策略  再给您答复  总统先生
We'll pursue other strategies and get back to you, Mr. President.

286
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:01,580
谢谢  罗伯特  福利改革怎么样了
Thank you. Robert, what's the latest on the omnibus?

287
00:19:01,590 --> 00:19:02,850
先生  法案再过
Sir, the legislation should go

288
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:04,640
两个月应该就能投票了
to the floor in the next couple of months.

289
00:19:04,700 --> 00:19:06,070
领导层有反对...
The leadership is pushing...

290
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:29,190
联系洛克希德和诺斯罗普[均为军工企业]
Set up calls with both Lockheed and Northrop.

291
00:19:29,190 --> 00:19:31,750
我们付钱让人接受培训  当做是工作
We'll pay people to get trained and call it a job.

292
00:19:32,450 --> 00:19:34,140
是不是工作工会说了算
It isn't a job unless the union says it is.

293
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:35,230
一步步来嘛
Well, one step at a time.

294
00:19:35,230 --> 00:19:37,740
你安排培训  我去找劳工联合会谈
You set up the training and I'll speak to the AFL.

295
00:19:37,740 --> 00:19:38,960
退休者协会的人来了吗
Are the AARP here?

296
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:42,360
在大堂  主席说他们要支持邓巴
In the lobby. The chairman told me they want to support Dunbar.

297
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:43,630
他们只是想敲打我们
They're just trying to rattle us.

298
00:19:43,630 --> 00:19:45,890
邓巴保证要挽救社会保险
Dunbar is promising to save Social Security.

299
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:48,610
从华尔街和政府浪费挤钱  而不是福利
Go after Wall Street and government waste instead of entitlements.

300
00:19:48,610 --> 00:19:49,670
叫他们进来
Well, get them in here.

301
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:51,320
这是打电话名单
You have your call list.

302
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,690
他们的会面还有十分钟才开始
Their meeting's not for another ten minutes.

303
00:19:52,690 --> 00:19:53,630
这就叫他们过来
Start bringing them over.

304
00:19:53,630 --> 00:19:56,130
他们那么老  走过来也得十分钟了
It'll take them that long to hobble over on their walkers.

305
00:19:56,970 --> 00:19:58,380
-弗兰西斯  -我去叫他们
- Francis? - I'll go get them.

306
00:19:58,390 --> 00:19:59,760
我只有几分钟
I only have a few minutes.

307
00:20:08,060 --> 00:20:10,380
你今天针对我是有意的
You singled me out today on purpose.

308
00:20:11,130 --> 00:20:12,990
-什么  -内阁会议
- What? - The cabinet meeting.

309
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:14,720
如果我要让你参加内阁会议
If I'm gonna invite you to cabinet meetings,

310
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:16,510
就不能小心护着你
there's not gonna be any kid gloves.

311
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,830
别说得像照顾我
Don't make it sound like a favor.

312
00:20:18,830 --> 00:20:20,810
你想去的  我同意了
You wanted to be there. I agreed.

313
00:20:20,810 --> 00:20:23,080
为了获得信息  做好工作
Well, so I could be informed and do my job.

314
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:25,850
那房间里的每个人都靠工作能力受到审视
Everyone in that room is judged by what they bring to the table.

315
00:20:25,850 --> 00:20:28,060
而你的工作不像样
What you brought to the table was amateurish.

316
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:31,390
凯茜和我一起提出了那个计划
Both Cathy and I proposed that plan.

317
00:20:31,390 --> 00:20:34,170
我一样也怪她  你当我是在针对你
I fault her as much as you. You're making this too personal.

318
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:35,860
是针对我
It is personal.

319
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:38,170
我觉得你是在为俄罗斯的事惩罚我
I think you're punishing me for what happened in Russia.

320
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:39,380
得了
Oh, come on.

321
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,770
你在飞机上说  任命我是个错误
Well, you said it on the plane. Appointing me was a mistake.

322
00:20:42,770 --> 00:20:44,850
你说的话更过分
Yeah, you said far worse things to me.

323
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:48,270
是啊  我也十分努力忘记那次的争吵
Yes, and I've gone out of my way to put that fight behind us.

324
00:20:48,270 --> 00:20:49,990
是吗  像对托马斯那样
Oh, really? Like with Thomas?

325
00:20:49,990 --> 00:20:52,110
我们把你吵醒  你就大吼大叫
When you screamed at us for waking you up.

326
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:54,210
-我才没大吼大叫  -你让我丢脸
- I didn't scream. - It was embarrassing.

327
00:20:54,210 --> 00:20:55,650
谁管他怎么想呢
Who cares what he thinks?

328
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:58,170
他是我们的客人  你就那么走进来
He was our guest and you walked in there like--

329
00:20:58,170 --> 00:20:59,700
我觉得你在无中生有
I think you're searching for things that aren't there

330
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:00,850
而对存在的问题又视而不见
and ignoring the things that are,

331
00:21:00,850 --> 00:21:04,100
-比如拍照那档子事  -天呐
- like this photograph flinching nonsense.  - Oh, Jesus.

332
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:09,650
-你要我辞职吗  弗兰西斯  -别说傻话
- Do you want me to resign, Francis? - Don't be ridiculous.

333
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:11,980
说出来吧
Just say it.

334
00:21:12,910 --> 00:21:14,880
你根本不希望我做大使
You never wanted me to be ambassador.

335
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,690
你记得你在飞机上对我说了什么吗
You remember what you said to me on the plane?

336
00:21:16,690 --> 00:21:18,570
你不该让我当上总统
You should have never made me president.

337
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:20,400
我当时生着气  我不是那个意思
I was upset. I didn't mean it.

338
00:21:20,540 --> 00:21:22,700
你就是那个意思  你觉得你造就了我
You did mean it. You think you made me.

339
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:25,340
不是的  我觉得我们是一个团队
No, I don't. I think we're a team, actually.

340
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,910
我们现在可不是
Well, we're not a team at the moment.

341
00:21:32,490 --> 00:21:34,360
真难以置信我们变成了这样
I can't believe we've become this.

342
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:37,870
-什么样  -跟其他人一个样
- Become what? - Like everyone else.

343
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,030
可以了吗  先生
You ready, sir?

344
00:21:43,030 --> 00:21:45,160
稍等一下  让烟味儿散去
No, just give me a minute. Let the smoke clear.

345
00:22:11,110 --> 00:22:11,940
什么进度了
Where are we at?

346
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:43,140
她换发型了
Her hair's different.

347
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:45,320
但...
But I--

348
00:22:47,260 --> 00:22:49,520
-这是在哪拍到的  -圣达菲
- Where was this taken? - Santa Fe.

349
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,810
我把搜索范围缩小到了那个城市
I've narrowed the search to focus just on that city.

350
00:22:51,810 --> 00:22:54,010
我只有这么多  但我觉得这个开头不错
This is all I have, but I think it's a good start.

351
00:22:55,340 --> 00:22:56,330
我该过去
I should go there.

352
00:22:56,330 --> 00:22:58,680
不行  这是三周前的照片
No. These photos are three weeks old.

353
00:22:58,690 --> 00:23:00,170
她可能只是路过那里
She might have been passing through.

354
00:23:00,180 --> 00:23:01,580
也可能还留在那里
Or she might still be there.

355
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:04,490
好吧  但如果你去问东问西  可能会打草惊蛇
Okay, but if you start asking questions, you might tip her off.

356
00:23:05,610 --> 00:23:06,710
那再找点信息来
Get me more, then.

357
00:23:09,740 --> 00:23:11,110
我的护照怎么样了
How's my passport coming?

358
00:23:13,260 --> 00:23:15,130
等你找到她  我就给你解锁
I'll get the lock lifted when you find her.

359
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:19,080
我给你看了我的进展
I've shown you some progress.

360
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:21,780
我也该看看你的进展
I think I should be seeing progress on your side, too.

361
00:23:21,990 --> 00:23:22,720
这不够
This isn't enough.

362
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:24,770
他们又逮捕了我的一个朋友
They just arrested another one of my friends.

363
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,690
-他们随时能起诉我  -嘉文
- They could charge me at any minute. - Gavin...

364
00:23:26,690 --> 00:23:30,290
我为了拿到这些  做了很糟糕的事
The things that I've had to do to get this much are fucked up.

365
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:33,300
准确地点
An exact location.

366
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:35,360
这是我们说好的
That was our deal.

367
00:23:42,140 --> 00:23:43,640
你能把监控视频拿给我吗
Can you get me the camera feed?

368
00:23:43,870 --> 00:23:45,260
系统有监控
The system's monitoring it.

369
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:46,250
我要
I want it, too.

370
00:23:51,590 --> 00:23:52,820
我会把链接发给你
I'll send you the link.

371
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,460
道格  这是莫里斯
Doug? This is Maurice.

372
00:24:29,860 --> 00:24:32,120
他会接手你  我要搬去西雅图了
He'll be taking over for me. I'm moving to Seattle.

373
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:34,060
我姐姐要自己开个锻炼中心
My sister's opening up her own PT center

374
00:24:34,060 --> 00:24:36,020
她希望我去入伙
and she wants me to be a partner.

375
00:24:36,630 --> 00:24:39,650
我要把所有客户都交给别人
I'm moving all my clients over to new folks.

376
00:24:40,220 --> 00:24:41,710
这样我能帮助过渡
So I can help the transition.

377
00:24:42,890 --> 00:24:44,250
真舍不得你走
I'll be sad to see you go.

378
00:24:46,580 --> 00:24:48,140
我去拿几根漂浮杆
I'll go get some bar floats.

379
00:24:48,950 --> 00:24:49,950
就回来
Back in a second.

380
00:24:52,250 --> 00:24:55,610
我这周四要请人来做客
Look... I'm having people over this Thursday.

381
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:59,490
在我家开个欢送会  你也来吧
It's a going-away thing at my place. You should come.

382
00:24:59,490 --> 00:25:01,370
-可以了吗  -嗯
- You ready? - Yeah.

383
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:03,800
具体情况发短信给你
I'll text you the details.

384
00:25:12,830 --> 00:25:14,330
我要那些大人物的钱
I want to go after the big boys.

385
00:25:14,330 --> 00:25:16,070
不仅是华尔街  还有沃尔玛
Not just Wall Street, but Walmart.

386
00:25:16,070 --> 00:25:17,630
沃尔玛别轻易动
I'd be careful with Walmart.

387
00:25:17,630 --> 00:25:19,200
你会在国会失去很多盟友
You'll lose a lot of friends in Congress.

388
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:21,020
那就逼他们选边站
Let's force them to take sides.

389
00:25:21,330 --> 00:25:23,100
包括杰姬·夏普
That means Jackie Sharp, too.

390
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:24,410
推出法案
Introduce legislation.

391
00:25:24,410 --> 00:25:26,850
她要么赞成  要么我们狠击她
She either votes for it or we hit her hard.

392
00:25:26,980 --> 00:25:28,220
所有有超过10%员工
Any corporation who has more

393
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:30,560
在领食品救济券的大公司
than ten percent of its employees on food stamps

394
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:33,740
都要涨薪  直到这个数目低于10%
has to increase wages until they're below ten percent.

395
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:37,580
谁有胆支持这样的法案
Who has the guts to sponsor something like that?

396
00:25:47,730 --> 00:25:48,570
道格
Doug?

397
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:51,900
嗯  我写份名单
Yeah, I'll put a list together.

398
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:53,380
你周末就能拿到
You'll have something by the end of the week.

399
00:25:53,430 --> 00:25:54,810
好  到时再聊
Okay. Talk to you then.

400
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:27,350
你来了
You made it.

401
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:29,840
是啊
Yeah.

402
00:26:30,870 --> 00:26:33,450
-来多久了  -10分钟
- How long have you been here? - Ten minutes.

403
00:26:33,450 --> 00:26:36,490
来吧  我们得让大家舞起来
Come on. We need to get people dancing.

404
00:26:36,510 --> 00:26:38,370
其实  我觉得我还是走吧
Actually, I was thinking that I should go.

405
00:26:39,130 --> 00:26:40,470
我就是过来跟你道别的
I just came over to say goodbye.

406
00:26:41,990 --> 00:26:44,570
不行  你哪都别想去
No. You are not going anywhere.

407
00:26:45,210 --> 00:26:49,310
你不非得跳舞  但你也别想跑
You don't have to dance, but you can't leave.

408
00:27:04,680 --> 00:27:06,000
就剩你还没醉倒
Last man standing.

409
00:27:09,090 --> 00:27:10,250
你回收吗
You have recycling?

410
00:27:10,410 --> 00:27:11,830
放在桌台上就好
Just leave 'em on the counter.

411
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:13,670
我明天收拾
I'll take care of it tomorrow.

412
00:27:19,050 --> 00:27:20,700
你不用帮忙的
You really don't have to help.

413
00:27:21,250 --> 00:27:22,160
我不介意
I don't mind.

414
00:27:24,690 --> 00:27:26,110
你真绅士
You're such a gentleman.

415
00:27:26,920 --> 00:27:28,140
这你不能确定
I don't know about that.

416
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:31,240
你不是绅士吗
Oh, you're not a gentleman?

417
00:27:32,370 --> 00:27:35,520
那就...有意思了
Because... that could be interesting.

418
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:17,180
我给你泡了牛奶咖啡
I made you a café au lait.

419
00:28:27,250 --> 00:28:28,140
怎么样
How is it?

420
00:28:28,570 --> 00:28:29,990
-还要加糖吗  -不用
- Need sugar? - No.

421
00:28:30,850 --> 00:28:31,900
很棒
It's perfect.

422
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:36,230
你的搬家工什么时候来
When are the movers coming by?

423
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:38,090
还有两小时呢
Not for a couple hours.

424
00:28:39,420 --> 00:28:41,840
要我帮忙打包剩下的东西吗
You need any help? Packing the rest up?

425
00:28:42,550 --> 00:28:44,760
不用  你休息吧
No. You just relax.

426
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:50,660
你昨晚似乎有点难过
You seemed a little sad last night.

427
00:28:52,530 --> 00:28:54,420
没有  就是累了
No, just tired.

428
00:28:54,620 --> 00:28:58,480
是吗  只是累了吗
Was that it? You were just tired?

429
00:29:03,470 --> 00:29:05,380
有个我很久没联络的人
Someone I haven't heard from in a long time.

430
00:29:07,210 --> 00:29:08,850
她联系我了
She reached out. It was--

431
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:10,460
我有点难过
It was a little hard.

432
00:29:14,050 --> 00:29:16,510
你昨晚不是因为可怜我吧
Last night wasn't 'cause you felt sorry for me, was it?

433
00:29:16,510 --> 00:29:17,370
不是
No.

434
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:22,500
昨晚是因为我今天要坐飞机走了
Last night was because I'm getting on a plane today,

435
00:29:22,500 --> 00:29:25,230
我可能再也见不到你了
and I'll probably never see you again.

436
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:26,540
何乐不为呢
Why not?

437
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:40,010
西雅图经常下雨  你知道吧
You know it rains a lot in Seattle, right?

438
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:14,390
你今天跟我去纪念馆吗
Are you gonna come with me to the memorial today?

439
00:30:16,060 --> 00:30:17,300
我一定要去吗
Do I need to be there?

440
00:30:17,490 --> 00:30:18,290
不
No.

441
00:30:21,610 --> 00:30:23,000
我现在忙死了
I'm buried right now.

442
00:30:24,320 --> 00:30:25,130
好吧
Fine.

443
00:31:02,830 --> 00:31:05,290
汤姆·耶茨最近怎么总在这儿晃
Why has Tom Yates been hanging around so much?

444
00:31:05,340 --> 00:31:07,030
他要给总统写书吗
Is he writing a book on the president?

445
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:09,210
我们都问过  他不肯说
We've all asked him and he won't say.

446
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:11,620
如果真是可很大胆
Ballsy move if it's true.

447
00:31:11,850 --> 00:31:13,940
嗯  我受不了他的文笔
Yeah. I can't stand his writing.

448
00:31:15,300 --> 00:31:16,510
你傻逼吗
Are you an idiot?

449
00:31:17,110 --> 00:31:18,550
有看法就傻逼了
I'm an idiot for having an opinion?

450
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:21,380
有什么可"看法"的  他文笔多棒
There's no opinions to be had. His writing is gorgeous.

451
00:31:21,380 --> 00:31:23,440
我的看法就是  我不觉得
Well, in my opinion, it isn't.

452
00:31:23,560 --> 00:31:26,010
自己购物单都写不好还说别人
Said the guy who can't write a grocery list.

453
00:31:26,580 --> 00:31:27,850
就等您了  先生
Ready whenever you are, sir.

454
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:36,140
今天是《社会保险法案》的80周年纪念日
Today marks the 80th Anniversary of the Social Security Act.

455
00:31:36,410 --> 00:31:39,940
它的存在时间  甚至超过了不少其受益人
It has survived longer than many of its beneficiaries.

456
00:31:40,070 --> 00:31:43,530
希望所有人都能活到它这个岁数
We should all be so lucky to live as long as it has.

457
00:31:43,980 --> 00:31:48,220
但当人活到80
But by the time the human body has circled the sun 80 times,

458
00:31:48,220 --> 00:31:50,390
青春和活力就已不再
its youth and vigor are gone.

459
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:53,940
关节疼  骨头变脆  肌肉退化
Joints ache, bones and muscles are weaker,

460
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:57,670
心脏的跳动也不如从前强健了
the heart doesn't beat with the same power it once did.

461
00:31:57,880 --> 00:32:00,690
我们所有人都最终得面对这一事实
All of us must face this truth eventually.

462
00:32:00,820 --> 00:32:04,510
到那时  我们就得把接力棒交给下一代
And when we do, we must hand the baton to the young.

463
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:06,420
那些等我们离世后
To those who have the strength

464
00:32:06,470 --> 00:32:09,210
有力量继续我们事业的人
to carry on our work when we are gone.

465
00:32:09,370 --> 00:32:13,230
这一点也是事实  社会保险在崩溃
Here's another truth: Social Security is dying.

466
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:16,140
如今  值其80岁之际  它必须向
Now in its 80th year, it must give way

467
00:32:16,140 --> 00:32:20,120
一个更年轻  更有力的新未来计划让位
to a new, younger, stronger plan for the future.

468
00:32:20,300 --> 00:32:22,950
这就是《美国就业法案》
That plan is America Works.

469
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:26,640
光是在华盛顿特区  我们就将失业率
In Washington DC alone, we've managed to reduce unemployment

470
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:31,420
削减了超过三分之一  2.5万人找到了工作
by over a third and put 25,000 people to work.

471
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:33,260
如果我们能在这么短的时间里
If we can accomplish so much

472
00:32:33,260 --> 00:32:35,850
在华盛顿做出这么大的成就
in so little time here in Washington,

473
00:32:35,930 --> 00:32:37,280
想象一下如果国会在全国范围内
imagine what we could accomplish

474
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:39,280
为《美国就业法案》提供资金
if Congress funded America Works

475
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:40,680
又将取得多大成就
nationwide.

476
00:32:40,680 --> 00:32:43,100
那就不是几万份工作了
We wouldn't be talking about thousands of jobs.

477
00:32:43,100 --> 00:32:45,400
而是数百万
We'd be talking about millions.

478
00:32:46,340 --> 00:32:47,430
今天下午晚些时候
Later this afternoon,

479
00:32:47,430 --> 00:32:51,130
我会前往罗斯福纪念馆  向那个80年前
I will visit FDR's memorial to pay my respects to the man

480
00:32:51,360 --> 00:32:54,870
推行了《社会保险法案》的人致敬
who ushered in Social Security 80 years ago.

481
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:59,000
我们致敬先人留给我们如今的世界
We honor the dead for giving us the world we inherited.

482
00:32:59,250 --> 00:33:01,590
但我们也得认识到
However, we must recognize

483
00:33:01,590 --> 00:33:05,490
如果让先人管束我们  就只有死路一条
we are doomed if we allow the dead to govern us.

484
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:09,680
谢谢  天佑美利坚合众国
Thank you, and God bless the United States of America.

485
00:33:10,340 --> 00:33:12,770
华盛顿NBC新闻
From NBC News in Washington,

486
00:33:13,110 --> 00:33:16,250
这里是《恰克·托德新闻访谈》
this is Meet the Press with Chuck Todd.

487
00:33:16,920 --> 00:33:18,500
早上好  欢迎收看《新闻访谈》
Good morning and welcome to Meet the Press.

488
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:21,590
我身边是亨特利和格里尔议员
I have with me Congresswoman Huntley and Congressman Greer.

489
00:33:21,590 --> 00:33:23,080
议员女士  我先问您吧
Congresswoman, let me start with you.

490
00:33:23,170 --> 00:33:24,910
总统今日在无线电讲话中
In the President's radio address today,

491
00:33:24,910 --> 00:33:29,220
称华盛顿的案例是全国的榜样
he said the model here in Washington is a model for the nation.

492
00:33:29,220 --> 00:33:30,130
您赞同吗
Do you agree?

493
00:33:30,490 --> 00:33:31,710
是的  恰克
I do, Chuck.

494
00:33:31,810 --> 00:33:33,390
我起初持怀疑态度
I was skeptical at first.

495
00:33:33,290 --> 00:33:40,090
{\an1}马萨诸塞州民主党众议员丽贝卡·亨特利

496
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:35,840
我父母都是社会保险的受益人
Both my parents benefited from Social Security.

497
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:38,530
我自己也一直指望它
And I've always counted on it for myself.

498
00:33:38,750 --> 00:33:41,870
但当我想到我的孩子  孙辈
But, when I think about my kids, and my grandkids--

499
00:33:41,870 --> 00:33:44,010
丽贝卡提出了一个好观点  几十年来
Rebecca raises a good point, one that we've been making

500
00:33:44,020 --> 00:33:45,830
我们在共和党内一直在提出这个问题
in the Republican Party for decades.

501
00:33:45,840 --> 00:33:48,380
但是  您虽然支持《美国就业法案》
And yet, while you support America Works,

502
00:33:48,380 --> 00:33:50,410
贵党党内大多持反对态度
most members of your party do not.

503
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:53,110
恰克  我向来不怎么喜欢弗兰克·安德伍德
Chuck, I've never been a big fan of Frank Underwood.

504
00:33:53,150 --> 00:33:57,030
但我华盛顿的家附近的公园从未像如今这么干净
But the park near my house here in Washington has never been cleaner.

505
00:33:57,030 --> 00:34:00,230
我光顾的干洗店本月雇了两名新员工
The dry cleaners I go to just hired two new people this month.

506
00:33:57,350 --> 00:34:01,230
{\an1}阿拉巴马州共和党众议员卡尔森·格里尔

507
00:34:00,230 --> 00:34:03,180
我送孩子去的日托所的员工翻了倍
The daycare I drop my kids off at doubled their staff

508
00:34:03,180 --> 00:34:05,720
这样每个孩子受到的个性化关注更多了
so the children can get more individual attention.

509
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:08,810
总统拿联邦应急管理署的钱或许是过分了
The president may have overstepped in taking FEMA money,

510
00:34:08,810 --> 00:34:13,100
但成功就是成功  《美国就业法案》成功了
but when something works, it works. And America Works works.

511
00:34:27,220 --> 00:34:34,140
{\pos(180.9,76.05)}进步的证明不是让富人更富有  而是令穷人不困苦

512
00:34:49,660 --> 00:34:59,660
{\pos(150,65.7)}他们有意建立个别人统治全人类的政府系统
还称之为新秩序  这早有先例  而且不算"秩序"

513
00:34:49,660 --> 00:34:59,660
{\pos(382,284)}{\an3}原话是指纳粹

514
00:35:19,100 --> 00:35:19,910
你好
Hello.

515
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,420
{\pos(247.2,145.8)}埃莉诺·罗斯福  美国首位驻联合国大使

516
00:37:27,170 --> 00:37:28,340
给他们钱
Promise the money.

517
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:30,770
用一切手段让他回心转意
Whatever you need to turn him around.

518
00:37:30,770 --> 00:37:33,160
我会批准从国际开发署拨款
I'll approve the USAID funds.

519
00:37:35,870 --> 00:37:37,410
你为什么改主意了
What made you change your mind?

520
00:37:40,730 --> 00:37:44,100
今天  在纪念馆
Today... at the memorial.

521
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:48,970
你知道最触动我的是什么吗
You know what struck me the most?

522
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:53,460
埃莉诺
Eleanor.

523
00:37:55,770 --> 00:37:57,590
她一个人在旁边
She was off by herself.

524
00:37:58,560 --> 00:37:59,510
孤身一人
Alone.

525
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:03,860
富兰克林也是  一个人
And so was Franklin. He was alone.

526
00:38:07,090 --> 00:38:09,260
他们之间隔着墙
And there was a wall between them.

527
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:14,930
那些僧人
The monks.

528
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:18,900
他们来几周了  我们从没谈起过他们
They've been here for weeks. We haven't even discussed them once.

529
00:38:21,150 --> 00:38:23,040
很美妙吧  他们的作品
It's beautiful, isn't it? What they're doing?

530
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:23,890
是啊
It is.

531
00:38:29,540 --> 00:38:32,280
弗兰西斯  我今天看他们看了一个多小时
Francis, I watched them for over an hour today.

532
00:38:32,950 --> 00:38:34,150
我一直在想着
And all I was thinking was,

533
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:36,570
我们为什么没有一起分享此刻
why aren't you and I sharing this together?

534
00:38:46,810 --> 00:38:48,760
我们得想想办法  克莱尔
We have to do something, Claire.

535
00:38:51,050 --> 00:38:51,830
我知道
I know.

536
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:57,410
你想怎么弄
What are you thinking?

537
00:38:58,170 --> 00:39:01,740
我本来的发色  像我初识弗兰西斯时那样
My natural color. Like when I first met Francis.

538
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:05,450
-这个吗  -对
- This color? - Yes. Exactly.

539
00:39:06,060 --> 00:39:07,500
好  请坐
Okay. Have a seat.

540
00:39:26,340 --> 00:39:27,880
我想再修修袖子
I want to take up the sleeves a touch.

541
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:30,290
我觉得很好了  谢谢
Oh, I think they're perfect. Thank you.

542
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:38,360
-怎么样  -真美
- What do you think? - Beautiful.

543
00:40:00,670 --> 00:40:01,510
我们今天聚集于此
We have gathered today

544
00:40:01,510 --> 00:40:05,100
重证弗兰西斯·J·安德伍德
to renew the vows between Francis J. Underwood

545
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:08,150
和克莱尔·黑尔·安德伍德的婚誓
and Claire Hale Underwood.

546
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:15,130
就在这座教堂
It was here, in this church,

547
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:18,760
28年前  在上帝面前
28 years ago, before God,

548
00:40:19,050 --> 00:40:22,310
你们二人首次向对方许下了誓言
that you two first committed yourselves to one another.

549
00:40:29,150 --> 00:40:32,200
愿这再次确认的承诺  能加深你们的爱情
May this renewed commitment deepen your love for each other,

550
00:40:32,610 --> 00:40:34,910
让你们的婚姻更加坚固  直到永远
and strengthen your eternal bond.

551
00:41:17,150 --> 00:41:19,390
克莱尔的父亲给我们买下了这栋房子
Claire's father bought us this house.

552
00:41:20,110 --> 00:41:23,840
我本想自己出钱  这事一直让我介意
I wanted to pay for it myself. That's always bothered me.

553
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:26,910
你不介意他为你首次竞选出资吗
You weren't bothered to let him pay for your first campaign?

554
00:41:26,910 --> 00:41:28,230
那是政治  不一样
Well, that's politics. It's different.

555
00:41:28,230 --> 00:41:30,090
筹钱要上天入地
You take money wherever you can get it.

556
00:41:30,690 --> 00:41:32,540
这是我们第一个家
No, this was our first home.

557
00:41:33,930 --> 00:41:36,620
-是个快乐的家吗  -拜托
- Was it a happy home? - Oh, please.

558
00:41:38,470 --> 00:41:39,070
我以为你带我来
I thought you brought me here

559
00:41:39,070 --> 00:41:41,080
就是想不再扯谎了
because we were gonna cut through the bullshit.

560
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:43,350
这本书要写的是《美国就业法案》
This book is supposed to be about America Works.

561
00:41:43,350 --> 00:41:45,510
你必须作为书的核心  否则无法成书
There is no book without you at the center of it.

562
00:41:47,470 --> 00:41:49,640
你信任我吗  还是不信任
Do you trust me? Or don't you?

563
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:51,980
你如果不信任我  就另找人写吧
Because if you don't, get someone else to write it.

564
00:41:51,980 --> 00:41:52,800
或者你自己写
Or write it yourself.

565
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:54,150
你不知道过日子
You don't know what it's like

566
00:41:54,150 --> 00:41:56,390
还得随时小心翼翼是什么滋味
to go through life looking over your shoulder.

567
00:41:56,740 --> 00:41:58,670
背负没人能理解的秘密
Having secrets no one would understand.

568
00:41:58,670 --> 00:42:00,210
我第一本书不是自己写的
I didn't write my first book.

569
00:42:02,910 --> 00:42:03,780
我的朋友
My friend.

570
00:42:06,060 --> 00:42:07,050
死掉的那个
The one who died.

571
00:42:08,390 --> 00:42:09,270
是他写的
He wrote it?

572
00:42:09,270 --> 00:42:12,010
前半部分  只给我一人看了
The first half. He didn't show it to anyone except me.

573
00:42:12,590 --> 00:42:14,580
在医院时  他求我销毁书稿
In the hospital, he asked me destroy it.

574
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:16,110
我告诉他我会的
I told him I would.

575
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:21,090
但他写得太好
It was too good.

576
00:42:22,170 --> 00:42:24,480
该写完  我就给写完了
It needed to be finished. So I finished it.

577
00:42:24,480 --> 00:42:25,790
并说是你独立创作
And took all the credit.

578
00:42:25,790 --> 00:42:28,510
是啊  是我写的结局
Oh, yeah. It's my part, the ending.

579
00:42:29,460 --> 00:42:30,790
才是人们记住的部分
That's what people remember.

580
00:42:32,010 --> 00:42:33,070
但那本书
But the book...

581
00:42:35,850 --> 00:42:37,000
我整个职业生涯
My entire career...

582
00:42:39,950 --> 00:42:41,350
都是基于一个谎言
It's all based on a lie.

583
00:42:42,300 --> 00:42:44,150
秘密不是你一个人的专属
You don't have a monopoly on secrets.

584
00:42:57,710 --> 00:42:59,600
这里地下埋了郁金香
There's tulips buried under here.

585
00:43:01,540 --> 00:43:02,860
克莱尔种的
Claire planted them.

586
00:43:07,820 --> 00:43:09,080
我一直
I've always...

587
00:43:12,230 --> 00:43:13,530
从最开始
from day one...

588
00:43:16,230 --> 00:43:19,440
就对她答应我的求婚感到羞耻
been ashamed she said yes when I asked her to marry me.

589
00:43:19,790 --> 00:43:20,580
为什么
Why?

590
00:43:23,360 --> 00:43:25,050
我觉得我配不上她
I didn't think I deserved her.

591
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:29,460
但我告诉你
I can tell you this, though,

592
00:43:29,460 --> 00:43:31,390
如果不是克莱尔  我就不能入主白宫
there would have been no White House without Claire.

593
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:33,670
遇见她成就了更好的我
I was half the man before I met her.

594
00:43:34,580 --> 00:43:36,280
但是  我很自私
But still, I've been selfish...

595
00:43:38,320 --> 00:43:40,510
那样向她索取
feeding off her the way I have.

596
00:43:41,230 --> 00:43:43,020
她清楚自己选择了什么
She knew what she was getting into.

597
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:48,340
或许吧  她比我更了解我
Probably. She knows me better than I know myself.

598
00:43:49,560 --> 00:43:52,780
先生  我们计划是6点15分起航
Sir? We're scheduled to fly out at 6:15.

599
00:43:52,860 --> 00:43:54,280
再过几分钟就得动身了
Should probably leave in the next few minutes.

600
00:43:54,290 --> 00:43:55,340
谢谢  密查姆
Thank you, Meechum.

601
00:44:01,140 --> 00:44:02,280
写吧
Scribble away.

602
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:15,400
他在房子前跟你说什么了
So, what'd he tell you in front of the house?

603
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:18,680
没什么
Nothing much.

604
00:44:18,930 --> 00:44:20,960
不管是什么  似乎挺动情
Well, it looked intense, whatever it was.

605
00:44:21,620 --> 00:44:24,790
瞧  这就是我不做大车的原因
See? This is why I don't ride in the van.

606
00:44:25,640 --> 00:44:26,760
这次不是坐了
You did this time.

607
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:32,320
有时候得让人静静
Sometimes you just need to leave someone alone.

608
00:44:32,830 --> 00:44:34,650
好吧  我懂了
All right, I got the hint.

609
00:44:35,700 --> 00:44:39,490
我是说他  不是我自己
I meant him. Not me.

610
00:45:05,670 --> 00:45:06,550
他们哪去了
Where are they?

611
00:45:07,530 --> 00:45:09,600
-谁  -那些僧人
- Who? - The monks.

612
00:45:10,330 --> 00:45:12,570
他们今天早些时候做完了  先生
Oh, they finished earlier today, sir.

613
00:45:13,860 --> 00:45:15,020
没了吗
So it's gone?

614
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:16,590
是的
I believe so.

615
00:45:17,990 --> 00:45:19,560
我都没来得及看到
I didn't get a chance to see it.

616
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:21,430
他们应该拍过照
I'm sure they took a photo.

617
00:45:24,240 --> 00:45:26,330
你能叫人给我弄一份吗
Will you ask someone to get me a copy?

618
00:45:26,820 --> 00:45:27,760
这就去  先生
Right away, sir.

619
00:46:38,230 --> 00:46:41,360
克莱尔  我差点没认出来
Claire. I almost didn't recognize you.

620
00:46:41,690 --> 00:46:44,090
是啊  我决定该做点改变了
Yes, I decided it was time for a change.

621
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:45,670
很迷人啊
It's very fetching.

622
00:46:45,980 --> 00:46:47,790
希望您不介意我不请自来
I hope you don't mind me crashing your party.

623
00:46:47,790 --> 00:46:50,830
当然不  我的手下说你不在市里
Oh, of course not. My staff said you'd be out of town.

624
00:46:52,150 --> 00:46:55,170
介意我跟卡斯皮大使单独谈谈吗
Would you mind if I borrowed Ambassador Caspi for a moment?

625
00:46:55,170 --> 00:46:56,110
请吧
Of course.

626
00:46:59,190 --> 00:47:00,780
你躲了我三周
You've been avoiding me for three weeks.

627
00:47:00,790 --> 00:47:02,370
我去了耶路撒冷
I had a trip to Jerusalem.

628
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:06,400
你答应给津巴布韦三千五百万
You promised Zimbabwe 35 million

629
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:09,200
让他们提出会坏事的无理条款
so they'd introduce the poison pill amendment.

630
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:11,500
-只是出于人道主义考虑  -不是的
- For purely humanitarian reasons. - No.

631
00:47:12,130 --> 00:47:15,110
这是你们第一次给津巴布韦援助
This is the first time you've ever sent aid to Zimbabwe.

632
00:47:16,030 --> 00:47:18,350
别乱牵线
Don't draw connections that don't exist.

633
00:47:18,910 --> 00:47:21,560
我们绝不会给决议案搞破坏
We would never try to sabotage the resolution.

634
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:23,010
美国是我们的盟友
The United States is our ally.

635
00:47:23,770 --> 00:47:24,950
是啊  我们是
That's right, we are.

636
00:47:25,530 --> 00:47:26,730
那就有点盟友的样子
So act like it.

637
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:28,150
什么
Excuse me?

638
00:47:29,180 --> 00:47:31,360
我丈夫已经正式批准
My husband formally approved

639
00:47:31,360 --> 00:47:33,570
向津巴布韦提供八千万人道主义援助金
our own humanitarian package for eighty million.

640
00:47:33,570 --> 00:47:37,140
他们明天就将撤回条款
Zimbabwe will be withdrawing the amendment tomorrow.

641
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:40,070
决议案进入投票时
And when the resolution goes to a vote,

642
00:47:40,560 --> 00:47:44,140
希望以色列像个忠诚的盟友那样表示支持
I expect Israel to support it like the loyal ally she is.

643
00:47:44,590 --> 00:47:45,730
而不是背信弃义
Not lie to us.

644
00:47:45,730 --> 00:47:48,030
这可不是博取我们支持的方式
That's not the way to solicit our support.

645
00:47:48,350 --> 00:47:51,180
我没想"博取"  我在要求
I'm not soliciting. I'm demanding.

646
00:47:51,840 --> 00:47:53,230
我可怜你  克莱尔
I feel sorry for you, Claire.

647
00:47:54,390 --> 00:47:56,590
你丈夫要你来说狠话
Your husband sends you to talk tough.

648
00:47:57,700 --> 00:47:59,860
但等约旦河谷出了岔子
But as soon as things go wrong in the Jordan Valley,

649
00:48:00,540 --> 00:48:03,120
他就会甩手不管  让以色列收拾烂摊子
he'll turn his back and leave Israel to clean up the mess.

650
00:48:03,660 --> 00:48:04,760
他根本没这个实力
He doesn't have the muscle.

651
00:48:04,990 --> 00:48:06,910
他没法让国会配合他
He can't even get Congress to work with him.

652
00:48:07,230 --> 00:48:09,580
你羞辱佩特罗夫后都不能支持你
Or back you up after you call out Petrov.

653
00:48:10,070 --> 00:48:12,360
他背叛了你  也会如此对我们
He turned his back on you just like he will on us.

654
00:48:15,030 --> 00:48:17,990
我丈夫是我见过的最勇敢  最有决心的人
My husband is the bravest and most resolute man I know.

655
00:48:19,240 --> 00:48:20,880
他的计划会成功的
He will succeed in this plan.

656
00:48:21,080 --> 00:48:21,960
勇敢
Brave?

657
00:48:22,500 --> 00:48:24,050
我在约旦河谷服过役
I served in Jordan Valley.

658
00:48:24,560 --> 00:48:27,000
我国总统和外交部长也是  他呢
As did the President and the Foreign Minister. Has he?

659
00:48:28,660 --> 00:48:32,340
你不过是举着枪  听命令
You held a gun and somebody told you where to stand.

660
00:48:32,820 --> 00:48:36,700
别把这跟三军统帅的重担搞混
Don't confuse that with the burden the Commander in Chief faces.

661
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:38,990
弗兰西斯曾下令杀人
Francis has given the order to kill.

662
00:48:38,990 --> 00:48:41,410
他曾下葬过他送入虎口的士兵
He's buried soldiers he's put into harm's way.

663
00:48:41,900 --> 00:48:44,740
每一天  他承受的责任
And every day, he wakes up bearing responsibilities

664
00:48:44,760 --> 00:48:46,620
都是你无法想象的
you can't possibly imagine.

665
00:48:46,980 --> 00:48:49,350
如果你来承担  你会崩溃的
They would crush you if they fell on your shoulders.

666
00:48:49,870 --> 00:48:51,560
你去告诉你的上级
So you talk to your superiors.

667
00:48:52,540 --> 00:48:54,560
等明天条款撤销
And when the amendment is withdrawn tomorrow,

668
00:48:55,260 --> 00:48:59,270
你必须支决议案
you will commit to supporting the resolution.

669
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:39,800
{\pos(242.4,234)}吾爱

670
00:49:40,170 --> 00:49:44,130
{\pos(188.4,68.4)}没什么是永久的
除了我们

671
